A '''roboticist''' was an [[Engineer/Legends|engineer]] who designed [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. [[Morgan Katarn]], a leader within the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], became a roboticist through self-study and designed his own multi-purpose [[Droid/Legends|droid]], [[WeeGee]].<ref name="Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire">''[[Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire]]'', opening chapter</ref>

A qualified roboticist was be able to install parts of a droid to another and fine tune them; when [[8t88/Legends|8t88]] [[Mission_to_Nar_Shaddaa_(5_ABY)|lost]] his [[limb/Legends|arm]], he retreated to [[Sulon/Legends|Sulon]], and a new arm from [[Model 88-series administration droid|another 88 unit]] was transferred to him; lacking an available roboticist, the droid installed it himself.<ref name="Dark Forces: Rebel Agent">''[[Dark Forces: Rebel Agent]]''</ref>

